I make things that create things to break things.


That's cool.. I guess. But why?

I enjoy breaking stuff computationally. Shoving items into small memory spaces, dual naming and pivotal exploitation are my favorite ways to use technology against itself.

Using a bit of hexorsism and a dash of artificial intelligent agents I have become rather good at discovering logic based vulnerable bugs in all types of applications.

I host a secure and private cluster offering the following services

Everything on this cluster is and always will be free of charge for everyone to use.

  • find

    SearX @ eas.ooo

    Searx is a metasearch engine, inspired by the seeks project.
    It provides basic privacy by mixing your queries with searches on other platforms without storing search data. Queries are made using a POST request on every browser (except chrome*). Therefore they show up in neither our logs, nor your url history. In case of Chrome* users there is an exception, searx uses the search bar to perform GET requests.

  • pad

    Etherpad @ eas.ooo

    Etherpad is a highly customizable Open Source online editor providing collaborative editing in really real-time.

  • msg

    Riot/Matrix chat server (global)

    Matrix is an open source project that publishes the
    Matrix open standard for secure, decentralised, real-time communication, and its Apache licensed
    reference implementations.

  • bin

    Private pastebin

    PrivateBin is a minimalist, open source online pastebin where the server has zero knowledge of pasted data. Data is encrypted/decrypted in the browser using 256 bits AES.
